            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Deae Corypheae <lb n="2"/>sive Caelesti <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>elius</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>Alexande<supplied reason="lost">r</supplied> <lb n="5"/>b<expan><ex>ene</ex><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iciarius</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ularis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> X <expan><abbr>gem</abbr><ex>inae</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/>Lupo et Maximo co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Gefunden in sekundärer Verwendung als Baumaterial beim Südosttor der spätantiken Befestigung. Viele Ligaturen. (B): Selem: Z. 2: Caelestis; Z. 3/4: Zeilenfall nicht angegeben; Saria; AE 1934; AIJ; Schallmayer - Eibl - Ott - Preuß; Selem: Z. 3: Alexand[er]; Šašel Kos: Z. 3: Alexander; Z. 4: le[g(ionis)].</p>
            </div>
